class.description: JEle Table에서 사용할 수 있는 컬럼

properties.description: Defines the indentation of the container. Setting it to true indents the list.

Defines the header text that appears in the control. Note: If the headerToolbar aggregation is set, then this property is ignored. If this is the case, use, for example, a sap.m.Title control in the toolbar to define a header.
Defines the semantic header level of the header text. This information is, for example, used by assistive technologies, such as screenreaders, to create a hierarchical site map for faster navigation.
Defines the header style of the control. Possible values are Standard and Plain.
Defines the footer text that appears in the control.
Defines the mode of the control (e.g. None, SingleSelect, MultiSelect, Delete).
Sets the width of the control.
Defines whether the items are selectable by clicking on the item itself rather than having to set the selection control first.
Activates the unread indicator for all items, if set to true.
This text is displayed if the control contains no items.
Defines whether or not the text specified in the noDataText property is displayed.
When this property is set to true, the control will automatically display a busy indicator when it detects that data is being loaded.
Defines if animations will be shown while switching between modes.
Defines which item separator style will be used.
Defines the direction of the swipe movement to display the control defined in the swipeContent aggregation.
If set to true, enables the growing feature of the control to load more items by requesting from the model.
Defines the number of items to be requested from the model for each grow.
Defines the text displayed on the growing button.
If set to true, the user can scroll down/up to load more items. Otherwise a growing button is displayed at the bottom/top of the control.
Defines the direction of the growing feature.
If set to true, this control remembers and retains the selection of the items after a binding update has been performed.
Defines keyboard handling behavior of the control.
Defines the section of the control that remains fixed at the top of the page during vertical scrolling.
Defines the multi-selection mode for the control.
Defines the items contained within this control.
User can swipe to bring in this control on the right hand side of an item.
The header area can be used as a toolbar to add extra controls for user interactions.
A toolbar that is placed below the header to show extra information to the user.
Defines the context menu of the items.
Defines the message strip to display binding-related messages.
Defines the custom visualization if there is no data available.
하단 Paging용.
Association to controls / ids which label this control.
Fires when selection is changed via user interaction. In MultiSelect mode, this event is also fired on deselection.
Fires when selection is changed via user interaction inside the control.
Fires when delete icon is pressed by user.
Fires after user's swipe action and before the swipeContent is shown.
Fires before the new growing chunk is requested from the model.
Fires after the new growing chunk has been fetched from the model and processed by the control.
Fires before items binding is updated (e.g. sorting, filtering).
Fires after items binding is updated and processed by the control.
Fires when an item is pressed unless the item's type property is Inactive.
Fired when the context menu is opened.
Sets the background style of the table. Depending on the theme, you can change the state of the background from Solid to Translucent or to Transparent.
Defines the algorithm to be used to layout the table cells, rows, and columns.
Setting this property to true will show an overlay on top of the table content and prevents the user interaction with it.
Enables alternating table row colors.
Defines the layout in which the table pop-in rows are rendered.
Defines the contextual width for the sap.m.Table control.
Enables the auto pop-in behavior for the table control.
Defines which columns should be hidden instead of moved into the pop-in area depending on their importance.
Determines whether the data export is enabled.
Defines the columns of the table.
Provides a message if no visible columns are available.
Fired when the context menu is opened.
This event gets fired when the user pastes content from the clipboard to the table.
Fired when the table pop-in has changed.
ex. fields='[ { "label": "넥스트웰", "value": "Ship-To"}, { "label": "Hyeonhee Kang", "value": "Owner Name"} ]' [{ label, value}] label/value: string | binding object

Displays date in this given type in input field. Default value is taken from locale settings. Accepted are values of CalendarType or an empty string. If no type is set, the default type of the configuration is used. Note: If data binding on value property with type sap.ui.model.type.Date is used, this property will be ignored.
If set, the days in the calendar popup are also displayed in this calendar type. If not set, the dates are only displayed in the primary calendar type.
Minimum date that can be shown and selected in the DatePicker. Must be a UI5Date or JavaScript Date object. Note: If minDate is after maxDate, they are switched before rendering.
Maximum date that can be shown and selected in the DatePicker. Must be a UI5Date or JavaScript Date object. Note: If maxDate is before minDate, they are switched before rendering.
Hides or shows the popover's footer.
Determines whether there is a shortcut navigation to Today. When used in Month, Year or Year-range picker view, the calendar navigates to Day picker view.
Determines whether the input field of the picker is hidden or visible. When true, the input field is invisible and can be opened by another control via openBy.
If set, the calendar week numbering is used for display. If not set, the global configuration is used.

Date Range with type to visualize special days in the Calendar. If one day is assigned to more than one Type, only the first one will be used. To set a single date, set only startDate of the DateRange class.
Internal aggregation that contains the inner picker pop-up.
Association to the CalendarLegend explaining the colors of the specialDates. Note: The legend does not have to be rendered but must exist, and all required types must be assigned.
Fired when navigating in Calendar popup.
Fired when value help dialog opens.
Fired when value help dialog closes.
